overview: Known for delivering classic pub rock, Dr. Feelgood cuts loose in this gritty homespun show, recorded live at The Mean Fiddler, London on August 20th 2005. Tracks are "Date Bait," "Too Much Trouble," "Baby Jane," "Roxette," "Milk & Alcohol," "Ninety-Nine & a Half," "I Can Tell," "Instinct To Survive," "Down by the Jetty Blues," "Back in the Night," "She Does it Right," "Going Back Home," "Down at the Doctors," "Waiting for Saturday Night", "Mad Man Blues" and "Bony Maronie".
title: Dr. Feelgood: Live in London
